Linux Commands

All Commands
Task 1: Check current logged-in user
whoami
id -un


Task 2: Check which users are currently logged in and what they are doing
who
w


Task 3: View login history of the system
last
lastlog


Task 4: Display complete system information, hostname, and uptime
uname -a
hostname
uptime
Additional useful command:
hostnamectl


Task 5: Create two groups (developers and qa) and verify
Create groups:
1
sudo groupadd developers
sudo groupadd qa
Verify groups:
getent group developers
getent group qa
Display complete group list:
cat /etc/group


Task 6: Create users and assign them to respective groups
Create users:
sudo useradd -m -G developers aman
sudo useradd -m -G developers ritu
sudo useradd -m -G qa karan
Set passwords:
sudo passwd aman
sudo passwd ritu
sudo passwd karan
Verify group assignment:
id aman
id ritu
id karan


Task 7: Delete employee ritu account with home directory
Check active sessions:
2
who
w
Delete user with home directory:
sudo userdel -r ritu
Verify deletion:
id ritu